{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Figure 3, the KG schema is constrained by the domain-specific ontology.",
    "The resulting KG has demonstrated better NER and relation extraction quality than the baseline KG Zhang et al. (2018); Purohit et al.",
    "An extracted node type follows a hierarchical schema to represent the most specific concept about the node.",
    "For example, GP E U rbanArea City represents a class City, which is a subclass of an urban area, itself a subclass of a geopolitical entity.",
    "Similarly, Conf lictAttack F irearmAttack represents an attack event related to some conflict that involves firearms."
  ]
}